# 📊 Enterprise AI Value Engineering Framework

A structured methodology for quantifying productivity ROI from enterprise AI platform deployments — 
designed for presales, value engineering, and strategic planning.

## 📖 Overview

This framework provides a repeatable, evidence-based approach to modeling the financial impact of 
AI agent platform adoption across large organizations. It is built around real trial data and scales 
from pilot groups to enterprise-wide deployment scenarios.

Use this framework to move stakeholder conversations from abstract capability to measurable 
business value — translating AI activity (chats, prompts, use cases) into hours saved, FTE 
equivalencies, and projected cost avoidance.

---

## 🧪 Trial Methodology

A structured pilot is the foundation of this framework. Key inputs from a representative trial group:

- **Participants:** A defined cohort of domain experts (recommended: 15–25)
- **Activity tracked:** Total AI-assisted interactions (chats/prompts) over the trial period
- **Productivity measurement:** Time saved per use case, captured via structured self-reporting
- **Quality measurement:** Accuracy/relevancy score (target: 80%+)

### Reference Benchmark (Anonymized Trial Data)

| Metric | Result |
|---|---|
| Participants | 17 |
| Total interactions | 755 chats |
| Average prompts per person | 44 |
| Average time saved per use case | 1.9 hours |
| Accuracy / relevancy score | 80%+ |
| Trial productivity value | CAD $143,450 |

> **Assumption:** CAD $100/hour as a conservative blended rate for knowledge workers in 
> regulated industries (insurance, financial services, professional services). Adjust to reflect 
> your target organization's loaded labor cost.

