## 🗺️ Phased Implementation Model

### Phase 1 — Months 1–3 | 100 Users
- Focus: High-frequency knowledge work teams (e.g., Product, Pricing, Customer Service)
- Expected quarterly ROI: CAD $872,100
- FTE impact: 4.47 additional productive capacity

### Phase 2 — Months 4–9 | 500 Users
- Focus: Expand to operational units (e.g., Claims, Underwriting, Risk Management)
- Expected quarterly ROI: CAD $4,360,500
- FTE impact: 22.36 additional productive capacity

### Phase 3 — Year 2+ | 1,500+ Users
- Focus: Enterprise-wide deployment with department-specific agent configurations
- Expected quarterly ROI: CAD $13,081,500+
- FTE impact: 67.08+ additional productive capacity

> **Conservative benchmark:** Phase 2 (500 users) represents a **10:1 ROI** within the first year 
> even after accounting for implementation costs and adoption curve friction.

